President Biden held a conversation with President Guillermo Lasso of Ecuador to discuss their shared vision for the Americas in anticipation of the Summit of the Americas. They emphasized the significance of the U.S.-Ecuador relationship and explored ways to enhance economic, security, and migration cooperation. COVID-19 response and recovery, as well as support for regional priorities, were also key topics of discussion. Both leaders expressed their commitment to promoting democratic values and advancing the objectives of the upcoming summit.